column252: Any thoughts or suggestions on INDENG courses?
column253: What advice do you have for current Berkeley students seeking job in your role?

Seeking a job in Software Engineering requires you to have knowledge of one course : Data Structures. Apart from that knowledge, it is simply a matter of cleaning up your resume, practicing Leetcode and applying to as many companies as you can. Good luck with your job searches!
Use your connections and go to company info sessions 👍🏼

column115: The ability to unpack business problem and form it into a data science problem

column253: My advice is to simply apply to as many openings as you can! Don’t be afraid to reach out via LinkedIn and ask for advice as well. Advice is often more valuable than things like referrals
Everybody starts at nothing, you will get there eventually with enough grinding
A ML developer/data scientist is only as good as they understand randomness & probability
start earlier, be patient, be prepared

column97: MIDS W203; Statistics for Data Science
column253: Focus on a specific domain rather than restricting to broader data science. Stay up-to-date on new research and work on applying new methods and skills continuously
Networking gives you a higher likelihood of landing a job
